## This guide explains how to install and run **Minikube** on an AWS EC2 Ubuntu instance.

Launch EC2 Instance
Instance type: t2.medium (at least 2 vCPU + 4GB RAM)
Storage: 20GB recommended

Step 1: Update Packages
sudo apt update -y
sudo apt upgrade -y

Step 2: Install Docker (Driver for Minikube)
sudo apt install -y docker.io
sudo usermod -aG docker $USER && newgrp docker

Step 3:Verify Docker Install
docker --version

Step 4:Install conntrack (required by Minikube)
sudo apt-get install -y conntrack

Step 5:Install Minikube
curl -LO https://storage.googleapis.com/minikube/releases/latest/minikube-linux-amd64
sudo install minikube-linux-amd64 /usr/local/bin/minikube

Step 5:Verify Minikube Install
minikube version

Step 6:Install kubectl (Kubernetes CLI)
curl -LO "https://dl.k8s.io/release/$(curl -L -s \
https://dl.k8s.io/release/stable.txt)/bin/linux/amd64/kubectl"
chmod +x kubectl
sudo mv kubectl /usr/local/bin/
kubectl version --client

Step 7:Start Minikube (with Docker driver)
minikube start --driver=docker

Step 8:Verify Installation
Check Status 
minikube status
kubectl get nodes
